 The Central Bank of Nigeria on Saturday won the 33rd edition of the Financial Institutions football competition by defeating the Unity Bank team 1-0 in the final. The match played inside the Pa Ngele Oruta stadium, saw the CBN team’s goal coming in the second half through a ‘contested’ penalty kick. The match was watched by over 2,000 fans including the competition’s Brand Ambassador and former Super Eagles Star, Victor Ikpeba. Continue reading Central Bank of Nigeria wins 33rd edition of financial institutions football competition at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard